originalText.text:
I learned about wink through a promotion that groupon offered. I followed all required steps to redeem the offer and secure an appointment. However, a day before my appointment I was contacted and asked if I could reschedule. How inconvenient!! My first thought was to just cancel and request a refund through groupon but I decided against it because I was having my lashes done for a special occasion. But I should have followed my first instinct!
The day of my appointment arrives and I arrive at the location to find that entering the facility was going to be a little difficult because the doorbell was broken. I waited a little while and was able to gain access when a delivery person exited. Once I arrived upstairs at the WINK office doors I spoke with the receptionist. The receptionist briefed me on their process and had me choose the length of the lashes I preferred. Then I waited for quite a long time. Once I was called I was ushered into a brightly lit room full of customer on various tables around the room having their lashes done.
The technician that I had definitely needed additional training. After the process was completed I definitely felt like I could have done better attempting the process on myself. I have had  my lashes done in the past but this was definitely my WORST experience. My eyes were sore and red after the process was completed. Also during the installation process the adhesive solution dripped in my eyes and caused them to burn. I had to have the technician stop several times due to irritation and a burning sensation.
I would never return to this place no matter how good the offer because I value my eyes and want to maintain my ability to see.

originalText.text:
Was a first attempt to eyelash extensions and I selected them based on reviews here and i saw someone's lashes first hand.

The staff was friendly enough and explained the process and maintenance. I opted for the wink set and paid the extra $10 for the mascara look. I was sceptical regarding the table set up and was upset that they continued to change who my appointment was with (Jade) during my initial and follow-up visit. But that doesn't take away from the great job Lisa did.

Unfortunately, this is an expensive guilty pleasure that i will only do from time to time, after the hair, nails and other beauty regiments.

But I recommend at least a one time experience should be attempted with the this diva beauty secret.

originalText.text: This review would have been excellent if I didn't feel tricked into spending more money. I got a deal for this business on Lifebooker (only way to do beauty services in my opinion!) and went to this place, which was a bit secluded, but the decor inside made up for it. It was almost like walking into a page from a fairytale, with lined up beds with pink quilts that the associates tuck you into. I received the mascara eyelashes, which were perfect for what look I wanted to achieve, but then I was told that the eyelashes were more than my package, which they did not tell me about before they were semi-permanently put on my eyes! Make sure you know what you're getting. That would be my only gripe.
